Class ScannerActivity

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback, ScannerListener

    public class ScannerActivity
extends android.app.Activity
implements ScannerListener
    Wrapper Activity for native VIN scanner library. Activity can function in two modes: single scan and continuous scan. In single mode the first scanned VIN-code is returned in intent. In continuous mode the scanned code is shown to user and then scanner continues the scanning process. Code to start Scanner activity in single mode: 
    
 Intent intent = new Intent(curContext, com.bees4honey.vinscanner.Scanner.class);
 intent.putExtra(com.bees4honey.vinscanner.ScannerActivity.SINGLE_SCAN, true);
 startActivityForResult(intent, SCAN_CODE);
    If Scanner was started in a single mode then you may use the following code to extract scanned code 
         
 protected void onActivityResult(int requestCode, int resultCode, Intent data) {
     if (requestCode == SCAN_CODE && resultCode == RESULT_OK) {
         String scannedVIN = data.getStringExtra(com.bees4honey.vinscanner.Scanner.SCANNED_CODE);
         Log.d("VinScanner", "Scanned vin: " + scannedVIN);
     }
 }

    • Field Detail

      • SINGLE_SCAN

        public static final java.lang.String SINGLE_SCAN
        Key for boolean extra which should be passed to the activity. If true then first scanned VIN code would be passed back to the calling activity with intent containing SCANNED_CODE activity. If no value passed with SINGLE_SCAN value then scanner is functioning in continuous mode.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
